Wanna know something cool?

There are hundreds of kilometers of evacuation tunnels linked underneath governmental building. Every nation's government, whether they be China or Russia or North korea.
Even in africa, there are routes. The equivalent of entire cities lay beneath the ground- and you may not even know it. This is the reason why most nations get angry if you
try and dig too deep in your lawn. Its not about cables- its about tunnels. Why do you think they dont extend your property rights deeper down into the ground?
Because they dont want you to find an emergency evacuation tunnel. 
The bigger and older the city, the richer the nation, and the more paranoid the government correlates to more tunnels. The parisian catacombs are a small fraction of the true tunnels-
coursing outward from paris like nerves. Leading to all manner of reinforced compounds, fortresses, and probably entire communities that have founnd themselves gathering.
Think, for a moment- the vastness of mines. Most mines are run by companies with a fraction of the wealth that an entire nation might have.
